<HEADLINE>City grace beats traffic snarl-ups</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>Advertising Feature</ARTICLETYPE>
<FLAG>SCOTLANDS HOMES,</FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>976633927</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
APART from the immediate and easy access to city centre amenities,
there are other attractions of living in a place like St Andrew's
Square. One very important part of its appeal is the convenience for
work.
''I think this marketplace has grown tremendously in the past few
years because of increasing traffic jams going into work,'' said Ronnie
McLetchie, City Link Director. ''Here there are no parking problems, and
the nearby subway can take you to other parts of the city within
minutes. There is also the investment aspect of buying a quality home.
In the Tannery Building, we have already sold a number of flats and,
over a two-year period, they have increased in value.''
City Link's developments around the square will consist of two, three,
and four-apartment flats, with the larger homes having a separate study
or dining room.
There are eight penthouse flats constructed on two separate storeys,
the third and fourth floors, connected by an internal staircase. All
have balconies overlooking the church and the square, with southerly
aspects over Glasgow Green. Each of the four styles, the Hermiston, the
Waverley, the Lockhart and the Ballantrae, are finished to a very high
standard, and each layout is unique.
While the Hermiston and the Waverley have a lounge, dining room/study,
kitchen and bathroom on the first floor, with two bedrooms and a shower
room above, the Lockhart and the Ballantrae have the master bedroom with
en suite, a second bedroom and bathroom on the first floor, with a
lounge/dining area, kitchen and toilet on the upper level. Prices for
penthouses range from #89,000 to #95,000, and private secure basement
car parking is #5000 extra.
All of the homes in City Link's second phase in St Andrew's Square
have standard specifications like fully fitted kitchens with the
materials selected in advance by the owner and featuring fully
integrated units including oven, ventilated cooker hood, hob,
fridge/freezer, and washer/drier.
The toilets, bathrooms and en suites are all tiled to full ceiling
height and again, the owner can choose the colour which will then be
co-ordinated with tiles. Fixtures and fittings come as standard. The
bedrooms have fitted wardrobes where appropriate and there are focal
point fireplaces in the lounge.
All of the homes have double glazing, and the latest in central
heating systems from ScottishPower -- an innovative ''wet'' electrical
system which, with its DualHeat electric combination boiler provides
all-year-round heating and hot water. Unlike most conventional electric
heating systems, it supplies hot water to a conventional radiator
system. Running costs are low because it uses the new Economy 2000
tariff.
There are elevators in all of the dwellings, running from the basement
to the top floor flats, and an electronic coded entry system. There is
also a security system which includes intruder, smoke and panic alarms.
The St Andrew's Square development has been built internally and
externally to a very high specification.
St Andrew's Square is well worth a visit, especially now that the
latest showflat has been opened. Prices for two-bedroomed flats there
start at #68,000.
For further information about City Link's St Andrew's Square
development, telephone 0141 552 8899 or 0141 334 3420.
</TEXT>
