<HEADLINE>Dokka proves to be the iron man</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>28</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976633928</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
NORWEGIAN-BORN Arne Dokka, winner of the United States public links
golf championship in 1965, headed the Shell Scottish Seniors Open
championship pre-qualifying competition with a two-under-par 68 at Royal
Aberdeen Golf Club yesterday.
A naturalised American -- his parents emigrated from Oslo in 1947 when
he was three years old -- Dokka, 51, has been a pro for the past 20
years and now plays out of Pinehurst Country Club, North Carolina.
Dokka's four birdies came mostly through accurate iron play, although
he did hole a 40ft putt for his first birdie. He dropped shots at the
twelfth and thirteenth, mainly because he was not sure of the right line
to the hole on what was only his second outing over the Balgownie
course.
''I love playing in Scotland and on Scottish links in particular and
it's great to be playing golf in nice, cool weather. It's been between
90[DEG] and 100[DEG] back home every day this summer,'' said Dokka.
Sixty players took part in the pre-qualfier, with only 25 going
forward to the 72-hole championship proper, which begins on Friday.
Seven men on 74 played off for the last six places, and Mike Ingham
(Cleckheaton) was relegated to the position of first reserve.
Ingham is one of the original Ernest Butten Boys from the 1960s.
Another one of them, new British Senior Open champion Brian Barnes, is
the hot favourite to take the Scottish title.
Top Scot was Andrew Gauld, now based at Lichtenau-Weickershof in
Germany. He shared second place on 69 with Harry Flatman, from Romford,
and Paul Leonard, from Dumurry in Ireland. Qualifiers:
68 -- A Dokka (USA).
69 -- A Gauld (Scotland), H Flatman (England), P Leonard (Ireland).
70 -- F Boobyer (England).
71 -- S Wilson (England).
72 -- M Moir (Scotland), B Browne (Ireland), S Maharaj (T&amp;T), I D
Smith (Scotland), J Hudson (England), F Hill (England), R Emery
(England).
73 -- J Wilkshire (England), K Magnusson (Sweden), D Melville
(Scotland), J Johnson (England), J Hume (Scotland), R Hurvitz (USA).
74 -- M Gunn (England), P Gill (England), A Bickerdike (England), F C
Agui (Spain), R Jetter (USA), R Webster (Scotland). Eliminated in
play-off -- M Ingham (England).
</TEXT>
