<HEADLINE>Brown hails a new Hansen</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>KEN GALLACHER</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>29</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976633942</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
UNDER-21s:
PETER Handyside of Grimsby was brought back into Scotland's under-21
squad yesterday, and was immediately tipped to be the ''new Alan
Hansen'' by national team manager Craig Brown.
Handyside, 21, missed the Toulon tournament in the summer, and was
absent from the Greek game two weeks ago while he shook off the effects
of an end-of-season injury.
Now, with skipper Steven Pressley suspended, Dumfries-born Handyside
makes a return as Brown indicates a partnership at the heart of the
defence with Dundee United's Christian Dailly, Scotland's most capped
player at this level.
Brown said: ''Peter is someone who likes to play football from the
back, and that is something that the Under-21 coach Tommy Craig and
myself want to encourage. He is the new Alan Hansen and we are glad to
have him back with the pool of players for this important game.''
The match could catapult the young Scots into the European
Championship quarter-finals if they can win. The only defeat they have
suffered so far is in Finland in the opening game of the group. Now a
revenge victory would put the youngsters through ahead of the Finns.
But Brown warned: ''This is almost as vital to Finland as the full
international because they can see the chance to qualify for the Olympic
games. That is as important to them as the European finals.
''But our lads have been going well since that opening match, and we
believe we can win this one.''
The game takes place at Broadwood next Wednesday with a 1pm kick-off
as an appetiser to the main hampden event. Squad:
Stillie (Aberdeen), Gardiner (Hibernian), Hamilton (Dundee), Baker (St
Mirren), Handyside (Grimsby), McNamara (Dunfermline), Crawford (Raith),
Fullarton (St Mirren), Glass (Aberdeen), Gray (Celtic), Hannah (Dundee
Utd), Harper (Hibernian), Locke (Hearts), McLaughlin (Celtic), Murray
(Rangers), O'Neill (Clyde), Dailly (Dundee Utd), Donnelly (Celtic),
Liddell (Barnsley), McCann (Dundee), Miller (Rangers).
</TEXT>
