<TEXT>
A GREAT deal of the important work on a KDL home is done before a
brick has been laid, for the company goes to enormous lengths to search
out sites where the quality of the environment will match the quality of
the housing.
The Moorings development at Cove Road, Gourock, shows just how well
this policy can pay off, for the site overlooks Cardwell Bay, with
stunning views across the Clyde to Cove and Kilcreggan, and the owners
will have the exclusive use of a deep water slipway just across the
road.
The scheme consists of 20 two-bedroom flats in five blocks, and so
that owners can enjoy the views across the Clyde, the homes have been
designed with balconies on all the upper floors, and with small private,
terraced gardens on the ground floors.
Prices range from #83,500 to #91,000. Once the flat has been selected,
a deposit of #250 secures the reservation at a fixed price. This deposit
is included in the final purchase price.
The Moorings fronts onto Cove Road, which is a cul-de-sac on the east
side of Gourock, just past Battery Park as you approach from Glasgow.
The site was bought by KDL homes in 1993. It had been occupied by local
yacht builder, but became an eyesore after the shipyard closed five
years ago.
The managing director of KDL Homes, Tom Paice, says: ''We have greatly
improved the visual appeal of the whole coastline and general
environment, while at the same time providing for owners at The Moorings
what I consider to be the finest view in the West of Scotland.''
KDL homes is an expanding company which specialises in building in the
Central Belt. It has established a reputation for distinctive, spacious
homes, constructed to the highest specifications, finished to the
highest standards and set in attractive surroundings.
The Dumbarton-based firm started business in March 1987 and has found
a niche market developing sites in Central Scotland of up to 40 homes in
places such as Strathaven, Busby, Helensburgh, Skelmorlie, Lenzie and
Falkirk.
KDL Homes is happy to customise their luxury homes to individual
requirements so long as this is indicated in advance. Colour schemes can
be coordinated, archways can be constructed, extra power points can be
incorporated -- in fact, all reasonable requests can be complied with.
At The Moorings in Gourock, there is a choice of three styles, A, B
and C. Styles A and B have a separate dining room, while style C has a
kitchen/dining room. Three of the five blocks of flats are two-storey
and the other two, which are larger, are three-storey. The two larger
blocks contain style C, and the homes on the upper two floors are
particularly spacious, with living rooms extending to 17ft 4in by 17ft
1in.
The Moorings development, set in a secluded area, offers luxury living
in an outstanding coastal location.
</TEXT>
