<PAGE>29</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976633948</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PAUL Gascoigne of Rangers is included in an England squad remarkable
more for a who's who of missing names for next week's rearranged
friendly against Colombia at Wembley.
There is no Paul Ince, Les Ferdinand, Warren Barton or Matthew Le
Tissier as Terry Venables gears up for the first of his European
Championship countdown games
Also out are Umbro Cup disappointments John Scales, Colin Cooper and
David Unsworth plus injury-hit Darren Anderton and understudy goalkeeper
Ian Walker.
But Venables has also included Stan Collymore, along with Gascoigne,
although injuries could rule out both.
But the biggest surprise is the inclusion of Coventry's summer
signing, 26-year-old winger John Salako, who is now given the chance to
resurrect his England career four years after a serious knee injury
threatened to put him out of the game. Squad:
Seaman (Arsenal), Flowers (Blackburn), Jones (Liverpool), G Neville
(Man Utd), Adams (Arsenal), Howey (Newcastle), Pallister (Man Utd), Le
Saux (Blackburn), Pearce (Nottm Forest), McManaman (Liverpool), Platt
(Arsenal), Lee (Newcastle), Redknapp (Liverpool), Batty (Blackburn),
Barnes (Liverpool), Gascoigne (Rangers), Wise (Chelsea), Sheringham
(Tottenham), Beardsley (Newcastle), Barmby (Middlesbrough), Collymore
(Liverpool), Salako (Coventry), Shearer (Blackburn).
</TEXT>
