<TEXT>
MELROSE are to embark on extensive developments at their Greenyards
ground, birthplace of seven-a-side rugby. An extraordinary general
meeting of the club decided that the #630,000 scheme should go ahead
once planning permission had been granted by Borders Regional Council.
Plans include moving the pitch four metres away from the stand. New
drainage and, perhaps, undersoil heating would be installed, as would
floodlighting, and the stand also would be developed.
