<HEADLINE>Don't break the bank</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>STEWART FRASER</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>25</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>FEATURE</ARTICLETYPE>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>976633959</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A SPORTY runabout, 14ft on the centreline, which goes behind the
smallest family car, contradicts the popular conception that boating is
for the rich. The Capri 1401 LS from Bayliner could be yours brand new
for #5995, including VAT. It takes four people back-to-back style, so is
handy for ski-towing, and has a galvanised trailer and 50hp outboard.
''I keep telling people that boating is not a rich man's sport,'' says
Stan Prosser, at Blochairn. ''Give people what they want. The right
boat, the right financing, the right guarantee. That's good business.''
The range is impressive too. Sports boats and cruisers from Bayliner,
Cruisers Inc and Bravo in the US, a trailable 16ft cabin cruiser from
Quayline in England and an interesting line in luxury cruisers from NB
Marine of Norway.
Moneywise, you can go all the way from a second-hand craft at #2500 to
a lottery winner's #200,000 super-duper dream boat. Stylewise, take the
14ft Capri, it's fine for swishing around in Loch Lomond, or off a quiet
coastline. Two seats face forward and two aft keep an eye on a skier.
There's an integral fuel tank, windscreen, instrumentation, lights, and
smooth inviting lines. An introductory model, if you like, leading to
the larger Trophy and then the Classic cruiser options.
These may well be for the fisher fanciers, with centre consoles and
protected cabins. There are other models that take more interest in
sleeping space and sunbridges, more in the family leisure mode.
Reach the motoryacht dream-line and this is big boat territory, with a
45ft or 47ft cruiser to play with. By now you can expect to get a flat
bowsprit construct -- really an extended pulpit -- to deal with
anchoring. Stereo systems, autopilots, radar, staterooms, home-from-home
galleys. If you pay more, you get more.
It's much the same idea with the Cruisers fleet. Their 42-footer
provides an adjustable helm seat and tilt wheel on the bridge just to
make sure you're comfy. Engine options go to 435hp or thereby. The
microwave oven is merely one part of a huge galley, and the television
is a built-in component of the integral entertainment centre.
With the Bravo line, we can go back to the sports boat concept. Speed
and style is of the essence. Getting on the plane is important and it
needn't preclude a stern swim platform, carpeting, or sport seating.
Typically, there is going to be rack and pinion steering, an automatic
bilge pump, power trim, drink holders, and ski storage among standard
features. You can add ice chests, a quick-plane extended hull, and gold
nitrate plated emblems if you choose.
Being able to trail a smaller boat on holiday makes sense for the
young family. Being able to trade in a runabout for a cruiser or fisher
suits the growing family. And those who have made it in business terms
can indulge their fantasies with whatever is biggest and best on the
market.
The real point is that a wide range of tastes, and expectations, can
be catered for today. First-time buyers have to be welcomed to boating,
encouraged to have a go, and looked after properly. That includes
judicious advice on safety at sea, basic boat handling if necessary, and
programmed maintenance needs.
''As far as I'm concerned, it covers finance, a parts and labour
guarantee -- our own one, no loopholes -- boat delivery, supervised
handover, and good insurance rates as well. Really, everything the
customer wants and is entitled to get,'' says Stan Prosser.
''This is a highly competitive business. I'm competitive and I take
this business very seriously. We'll be selling a total of 400 boats this
year, and that makes us one of the biggest marine traders in the whole
of the UK.
''As I say, go for down-to-earth prices, for down-to-earth people. And
that gets them down to the sea as well,'' he adds. ''That's what it's
about -- customer satisfaction.''
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH950830-000037</DOCNO>
