<DATE>950830</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Charity auction at Hansel Village</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>19</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976633976</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AYRSHIRE farmers have donated more than 200 prime lambs, 40 breeding
sheep, 100 beef calves, 60 store cattle and 30 pedigree cattle for a
charity auction to be held on Saturday in aid of the Hansel Village at
Symington.
The auction will be held at James Craig's new cattle market at
Whitefordhill, by Ayr, and the proceeds will go towards the #500,000
redevelopment of Wilson House, one of the Hansel's residential units.
A similar event was held 32 years ago when comedian Bob Monkhouse and
radio and TV personality Ted Moult help to raise #20,000 for the
building of a new residential unit, still known as Farmers House.
Judith Young, one of the organisers, said: ''We hope the public will
turn out in force to support the auction and all the other attractions
which will be laid on to make it an all-round family day.''
</TEXT>
