<DOCNO>GH950830-000086</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950830-000086</DOCID>
<DATE>950830</DATE>
<HEADLINE>What about the fathers' responsibilities?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>14</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>976634009</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TWO letters from males on the row over single mothers -- no mention of
the responsibility of the fathers (August 23).
Time for parents of sons to tell them not to indulge until they can
afford to support a child and its mother? And that that support has to
go on for at least 16 years.
Why should taxpayers subsidise the pleasures of a few minutes, of a
male, for 16 years? Parents must tell sons to take secure precautions or
not indulge till marriage.
Alice McColl,
Muir Lan Morrach,
Rhu Road, Arisaig.
</TEXT>
