<TEXT>
MAY I remind John Macleod of the battle-cry of the Covenanters at the
Battle of Philiphaugh? ''Christ and no quarter!''
None was given. Every man, every woman, and every child was put to the
sword.
One of the Covenanters' military leaders turned, in disgust, to those
shocking Presbyterian ministers who had insisted on the slaughter, and
asked: ''Have ye not had enough blood for one day?''
Robert Jamieson,
5 Chestnut Avenue,
Beith.
</TEXT>
