<TEXT>
SATURDAY's Herald Essay by John Macleod is so true that I had to write
my thanks.
We live in very dangerous times, but we are still free. We still have
God's Word in the Bible. It is vital that we pray for our Lord to aid us
in the battle and guide us into truth. We Scots used to be called the
people of the Book. Let us return to God's Word, the Bible.
I will also pray for our Queen, Country, and Commonwealth and an end
to European federalism which would be slavery.
