<HEADLINE>Aids drug trial</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976634071</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BANGKOK: A joint Thai-US military medical team has launched a trial of
a drug which might prove to be a preventive vaccine for Aids. More than
1200 Thai volunteers will help test the drug over five to six years to
see if it can stimulate the body to produce antibodies to the HIV virus.
In America, 2000 have tried the vaccine with no side effects.
</TEXT>
