<DATE>950830</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Jumbo idea</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976634073</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
JOHANNESBURG: A South African film company has found a novel way to
encourage people to plant trees -- by sending seeds wrapped in elephant
dung through the post. Dung from elephants at Pretoria zoo has been used
to make rough, fibrous paper which is folded into envelopes containing
three Bushveld Willow seeds for planting on Arbour Day, September 1. The
package -- seeds and manure -- can be planted together.
</TEXT>
