<TEXT>
COPENHAGEN: Danish police charged a television crew with complicity
after it filmed the biggest jailbreak in Denmark's history. The TV-Stop
cameraman, his assistant, and a photographer had received a tip-off and
were waiting outside the prison when a bulldozer smashed through a wall,
allowing 12 of the country's most dangerous convicts to escape. Nine are
still at large.
