<DOCNO>GH950830-000164</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950830-000164</DOCID>
<DATE>950830</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Australia makes visas easier</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976634087</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CANBERRA: Australia, often criticised abroad for its tight immigration
regulations, is to expand a streamlined system aimed at making visa
applications easier for tourists and business visitors.
The system, under which short-term visitors can obtain visas through
accredited travel agents, will be introduced in several more countries
by the end of the year, said Tourism Minister Michael Lee and
Immigration Minister Nick Bolkus yesterday.
The programme will be extended over the next few months to include
Denmark, France, Germany, Greece, Indonesia, Italy, the Netherlands, and
Tahiti. Talks had also started aimed at including South Africa, more
European countries, and North America.
The programme already operates in Hong Kong, Japan, South Korea,
Malaysia, Singapore, Slovenia, and Britain.--Reuter.
</TEXT>
