<TEXT>
MARSEILLES: A deputy to the mayor of Toulon, the first big French town
ruled by the far-right National Front, was found dead yesterday with a
suspicious head injury. Police have not ruled out foul play in the death
of Jean-Claude Poulet-Dachary, who had been attacked twice in recent
