<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976634090</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PARIS: A French high-speed train was evacuated after a false bomb
alert yesterday, three days after a powerful unexploded bomb was found
alongside a TGV track. The train stopped shortly after leaving Paris for
Lille and its 200 passengers transferred to another train while a
fruitless search took place. France has had a flood of bomb scares and
hoaxes since two bombings in Paris by suspected Algerian terrorists
killed seven people.
