<HEADLINE>Rebels blamed for massacre</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976634091</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BOGOTA: Marxist guerrillas are suspected to have gunned down at least
25 people yesterday in Colombia's north-western Uraba region, the third
massacre in the notoriously violent region this month.
Police said the guerrillas raided a banana plantation near the town of
Carepa shortly after dawn and rounded up about 25 people heading for
work in the fields, shooting them on sight. Nearly 40 people were killed
in two previous rampages by right-wing paramilitary gunmen.
