<HEADLINE>First victory for Hall</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>12</PAGE>
<FLAG>SPORT</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>976634126</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CAROLINE Hall defied near gale-force winds yesterday on her way to a
career-best closing round of 64 and a maiden American Express Tour
victory in the Ford Stimoral Danish Open at Vejle.
The 21-year-old from Bristol set a new Tour record for a 54-hole
tournament with her 15-under-par aggregate of 201, which left her eight
strokes clear of Australian Corinne Dibnah. Dale Reid was the best of
the Scots, when a 69 pulled her up into a share of fifth place.
Afterwards, Hall, a former Curtis Cup player, said: ''I was nervous at
the start of the day and felt I had to put pressure on Corinne. And she
gave me an opening when she took three putts on the first green.''
At the same hole, Hall hit a wedge third shot to eight feet for a
birdie 4, then holed from 20 feet for a 2 at the short second hole on
her way to the turn in 32.
She then holed another 20-footer for a birdie at the tenth and sealed
her first win since turning professional two years ago with birdies at
three of the last four holes.
