<HEADLINE>UN prepares revenge</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>1</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>976634130</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE British UN Commander in Bosnia, General Rupert Smith, yesterday
prepared retaliatory action aimed at punishing the Bosnian Serbs for the
mortar attack of a Sarajevo market which killed 37 people and wounded
more than 80. The UN said it had been confirmed Bosnian Serb forces were
responsible. In London, Mr Major was contacted by French President
Jacques Chirac and spent 15 minutes discussing the Bosnian crisis,
Downing Street said.
</TEXT>
